Interface GeneratedFiles

All Known Implementing Classes:
FileSystemGeneratedFiles, InMemoryGeneratedFiles
public interface GeneratedFiles
Repository of generated files. Can be used to add source, resource, or class files generated during ahead-of-time processing. Source and resource files are written using UTF-8 encoding.
Since:
6.0
Author:
Phillip Webb, Brian Clozel, Stephane Nicoll
See Also:

    • handleFile

      void handleFile(GeneratedFiles.Kind kind, String path, ThrowingConsumer<GeneratedFiles.FileHandler> handler)
      Handle a generated file of the specified GeneratedFiles.Kind with the given handler. The file handler lets you consume the content of the already generated file, if any and provide a way to override its content if necessary.
      Parameters:
      kind - the kind of file
      path - the relative path of the file
      handler - a consumer of a GeneratedFiles.FileHandler for the file
      Since:
      6.2
